The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bangla clinch ODI series
                                                                                                                       7                                      Bangla clinch ODI series
                      
	Dhaka: Captain Shakib-al Ha-san smashed a magnificent ce-ntury as Bangladesh beat New Zealand by nine runs in their fourth one-day match on Thur-sday to take an unassailable 3-0 lead in the five-match series.         
	Bangladesh reached an innings total of 241 before dismissing New Zealand for 232 with three balls to spare at the Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium. The hosts had won the first and third match while the second game was abandoned due to rain. The final game is scheduled for October 17.         
	New Zealand lost five wickets for 80 but recovered well to reach 150 for six. However, their last three wickets went for just seven runs as the visitors fell short of the target.         
	Opener B.J. Watling was the first victim as he was trapped lbw by Abdur Razzak for six.         
	Bangladesh skipper Hasan claimed three wickets  Grant Elliott (22), Aaron Redmond (16) and Daryl Tuffey (0)  conceding 54 runs.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                 
